Amitabh Bachchan was the first ever living Asian to make it to London's prestigious Madame Tussaud's in 2000, followed by Washington, New York, Bangkok and Hong Kong.
And now again he's being waxed!
Big B tweeted this picture of the measurement procedure last night captioned 'I get Madame Tussaud's again .. they replenish ..'
The destination of this latest statue is yet to be revealed but just the news of it has gotten the entire nation excited.
Here's yet another proof that there never was, is and never will be a bigger superstar than Amitabh Bachchan.
